---
// /sdk/model-viewer/quickstart — Quickstart for @splatforge/model-viewer.
//
// Companion to /sdk. Custom-element shim that teaches Google's
// <model-viewer> to render Gaussian-Splat .glb payloads alongside
// its existing glTF support — no fork of model-viewer, no eject.
import Base from "../../../layouts/Base.astro";

const title = "model-viewer plugin — SplatForge SDK quickstart";
const description =
  "Quickstart for @splatforge/model-viewer. Drop one <script> tag into your page, then point <model-viewer src> at a SplatForge-optimized .glb.";
---

<Base title={title} description={description}>
  <nav class="nav" aria-label="Primary">
    <a href="/" class="nav-brand">
      <span class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
      splatforge
    </a>
    <div class="nav-links">
      <a href="/">Home</a>
      <a href="/bench">SplatBench</a>
      <a href="/pricing">Pricing</a>
      <a href="/sdk" aria-current="page">SDK</a>
      <a href="https://github.com/montabano1/SplatForge" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">GitHub ↗</a>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <div class="breadcrumb">
    <a href="/sdk">← SDK overview</a>
  </div>

  <header class="hero hero-sdk">
    <h1>&lt;model-viewer&gt; quickstart</h1>
    <p>
      <code>@splatforge/model-viewer</code> is a custom-element shim
      that teaches Google's <code>&lt;model-viewer&gt;</code> to render
      Gaussian-Splat payloads. Existing <code>.glb</code> meshes keep
      rendering through the stock pipeline; SplatForge-optimized
      <code>.glb</code>s route through the splat renderer transparently.
    </p>
  </header>

  <section class="quickstart">
    <h2>1. Drop two script tags in your page</h2>
    <pre><code set:html={`&lt;script type="module" src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/model-viewer/4.0.0/model-viewer.min.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;script type="module" src="https://cdn.splatforge.dev/sdk/model-viewer@1/splatforge-model-viewer.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;`} /></pre>

    <h2>2. Point &lt;model-viewer&gt; at a SplatForge-optimized .glb</h2>
    <pre><code set:html={`&lt;model-viewer
  src="/assets/bonsai.splatforge.glb"
  camera-controls
  exposure="1"
  shadow-intensity="1"
  style="width:100%;height:480px;background:#0b0d10;"&gt;
&lt;/model-viewer&gt;`} /></pre>

    <p>
      The shim auto-detects the SplatForge extension in the
      <code>.glb</code> and swaps in the splat renderer for that
      payload. No other code changes — every existing
      <code>&lt;model-viewer&gt;</code> attribute (camera-controls,
      auto-rotate, environment-image, etc.) keeps working.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Bundler install (optional)</h2>
    <p>
      If you bundle your own scripts instead of pulling from the CDN:
    </p>
    <pre><code>npm install @google/model-viewer @splatforge/model-viewer</code></pre>
    <pre><code set:html={`import "@google/model-viewer";
import "@splatforge/model-viewer"; // side-effect import: registers the splat shim`} /></pre>

    <h2>4. Issue a license key (above 10k MAU)</h2>
    <p>
      Below 10k MAU per app per month the plugin runs without a key.
      Above the free tier, issue an HMAC-SHA256 JWT bound to your
      <code>Origin</code> domain:
    </p>
    <pre><code set:html={`curl -X POST https://splatforge.dev/api/v1/sdk/license \\
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $SPLATFORGE_API_KEY" \\
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \\
  -d '{"origin": "https://your-app.example.com"}'`} /></pre>
    <p>
      Pass it via a meta tag (auto-discovered by the shim):
    </p>
    <pre><code set:html={`&lt;meta name="splatforge:license" content="eyJhbGciOi…"&gt;`} /></pre>
  </section>

  <section class="next-steps">
    <h2>Next</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/sdk">SDK overview &amp; pricing</a></li>
      <li><a href="/pricing">Hosted optimize API pricing</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/montabano1/SplatForge" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Source on GitHub ↗</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .breadcrumb {
    max-width: 64rem;
    margin: 1.5rem auto 0;
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }
  .breadcrumb a { color: inherit; opacity: 0.7; }
  .quickstart, .next-steps {
    max-width: 64rem;
    margin: 2rem auto;
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
  }
  .quickstart h2, .next-steps h2 { margin-top: 2rem; }
  .quickstart pre {
    overflow-x: auto;
    padding: 1rem;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04);
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
  }
  .next-steps ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; }
  .next-steps li { margin: 0.5rem 0; }
</style>
